================
X. Prerequisites
================

X.X. Windows
------------

Make sure the following software is installed:

    Visual Studio Express 2013
    Arduino IDE

To make use of virtual MIDI ports, use the following 3rd party software:

    Go to http://www.tobias-erichsen.de/
    Download and install loopMIDI
    Download the virtualMIDI SDK
    Copy the following virtualMIDI SDK C files to the ThirdParty directory:
        teVirtualMidi.h
        teVirtualMidi32.lib


X.X. Linux (Fedora 20)
----------------------

Make sure the following packages are installed:

    g++ (>= 4.8)
    arduino
    alsa-lib-devel
    bluez-libs-devel
        bluetooth.h typeof -> __typeof__ for C++
        http://marc.info/?l=linux-bluetooth&m=133095314426234


X.X. All Platforms
------------------

Pair your PC with the Arduino's Bluetooth module using the PIN 1234.

Copy all directories inside Arduino/libraries to your Arduino installation's
libraries directory.

